external_knowledge:
- Business units are organizational entities within a company that are responsible for specific business operations; 
- Consumers are entities (households or businesses) that use energy provided by the company; 
- Energy metrics include various measurements related to energy consumption and production (e.g., yearly net energy offtake, connection power, PV power); 
- Renewable sources (e.g., solar, wind) are used to generate energy; 
- Cumulative energy consumption and average peak demand are calculated within the context of each business unit.

sql:
SELECT bus_id, COUNT(consumer_id) AS number_of_consumers
FROM consumers
GROUP BY bus_id;

SELECT consumer_name
FROM consumers
ORDER BY consumer_name ASC;
